        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 1:16PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 116 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ashridge, or 11 miles east of Haleyville, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brushy Lake, Moreland, Ashridge, Sipsey River Rec Area, Upshaw, and
Grayson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
